Quote:  Here [at Taeri] was the tall and graceful black pine; the manukau, a shrub like the [Victorian] tea-tree scrub, only more greenly leaved; a few broad leaved grass-trees; the mappo, the kolu, the red pine, and others too numerous for me to remember; but their leaves were ... delightful to one accustomed to the dingy foliage of Victorian forests. ...In charming variety were the elegant grass-tree, [sic] whose palm-like tufts of long rapier blade-shaped leaves hung gracefully over the tall slender stems.
Notes:  1861 Sep 27 Tuapeka in NZ Goldfields 1861 (1976) 23 [Pseud?dracoph?]

